SB1732 HFLR Page 4
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 B. The Board shall base its schedule of fees upon the
2 reasonable costs of review and inspection services rendered in
3 connection with each license, permit, or review, but such fees shall
4 be within the ranges specified in paragraph 2 of subsection A of
5 this section, except as otherwise specified in this section or as
6 provided by law. The Board shall establish a system of training for
7 all personnel who render review and inspection services in order to
8 assure uniform statewide application of rules. The Board shall
9 include the reasonable costs associated with such training in the
10 fees provided for in this section.
11 C. The Board may exempt by rule any class of licensee or
12 permittee from the requirements of the fee schedule if the Board
13 determines that the creation of such a schedule for any such class
14 would create an unreasonable economic hardship.
15 D. All fee changes adopted by the Board shall be reviewed and
16 approved as provided in subsection F E of Section 308 of Title 75 of
17 the Oklahoma Statutes.
18 E. Unless otherwise provided, licenses and permits issued by
19 the Construction Industries Board shall be for a one-year period.
20 F. When, at the time of application or renewal of any license
21 or registration, payment is made by check for fees and the check is
22 not paid by the bank on which drawn for any reason, such license or
23 registration issued at that time shall be invalid. In all such
24 cases, the license or registration shall be subject to the license
