9 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1686.1, is
10 amended to read as follows:
11 Section 1686.1. A. The Construction Industries Board is hereby
12 authorized to establish a license category for contractors who
13 solely perform poultry house premise wiring for environmentally
14 controlled poultry house systems, and the insured poultry house
15 wiring to connect the premise wiring, and who do not perform any
16 wiring for a structure or electrical facility that is not directly
17 involved in the operation of the environmentally controlled poultry
18 house wiring system. In addition to other statutory authority, the
19 Construction Industries Board shall have the power to exercise all
20 incidental powers and duties necessary to effectuate the provisions
21 of the poultry house contractor license, conduct investigations
22 involving compliance with the licensing requirements, and enforce
23 the licensing provisions of this section. However, the Construction
24 Industries Board is not authorized to conduct an electrical code
SB1732 HFLR Page 6
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 insp ection of an environmentally controlled poultry house premise
2 wiring system for purposes of compliance with electrical code
3 installation standards established for the Electrical License Act or
4 to issue administrative citations or fines concerning electrical
5 code installation standards at an environmentally controlled poultry
6 house.
7 1. With a valid poultry house contractor license, no further
8 registration or license is required under this act the Electrical
9 License Act in order to solely perform poultry house wiring for
10 environmentally controlled poultry houses. This license allows
11 contracting only for wiring of environmentally controlled poultry
12 house systems and is not intended to disallow or exclude unlimited
13 electrical contractors from performing poultry house wiring work
14 under an unlimited electrical contractor license without a poultry
15 house contractor license.
16 2. Experience under the poultry house contractor license shall
17 not be considered qualifying electrical experience for purposes of
18 experience requirements for application of any other electrical
19 license category pursuant to the Electrical License Act.
20 3. The Board may rely upon proof of a valid construction
21 license or registration issued by another state to expedite the
22 processing of the required information for a poultry house
23 contractor license;, provided, the insurance and workers’
24
SB1732 HFLR Page 7
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 comp ensation requirements demonstrate compliance with the required
2 coverage for work performed in this state.
3 4. All licenses shall be nontransferable, and it shall be a
4 misdemeanor for any business entity holding a poultry house
5 contractor license under the provisions of the Electrical License
6 Act to loan or allow the use of such license by any other person,
7 firm, or corporation, except as specifically provided in the
8 Electrical License Act or to engage in poultry house contractor
9 license work without a valid license pursuant to this act the
10 Electrical License Act.
11 B. A nonrefundable fee in the amount of Three Hundred Dollars
12 ($300.00) set forth in Section 1000.5 of this title for the annual
13 poultry house contractor license shall be paid at the time of
14 license application to the Construction Industries Board. The
15 annual license shall expire one (1) year from the date of issuance.
16 A poultry house contractor license shall be issued for one (1) year,
17 at which time it may be renewed upon meeting the requirements of
18 this section, making application, and paying the nonrefundable
19 license renewal fee in the amount of Two Hundred Dollars ($200.00)
20 set forth in Section 1000.5 of this title.
21 C. The Construction Industries Board shall, upon proper
22 application and payment of fee, license and issue a certificate of
23 poultry house contractor license to any person who furnishes
24 satisfactory proof to the Board that the applicant:
SB1732 HFLR Page 8
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 1. Is eighteen (18) years of age or over;
2 2. Is the party performing, overseeing, or otherwise
3 responsible for the poultry house contractor work performed and who
4 meets all requirements of this act the Electrical License Act and
5 resulting rules required to obtain such license; and
6 3. Has provided all necessary information and documentation
7 required under this act the Electrical License Act, the resulting
8 rules, and as requested by the Board.
9 D. The Construction Industries Board shall require the
10 following for a poultry house contractor license:
11 1. The applicant’s full legal name, physical address, mailing
12 address, business name, telephone number of business and applicant,
